title: Cross section for non-Rutherford backscattering of He-4 from five light elements

from five light elements

x4freetext: A thin film of the measured element was deposited on a
self-supporting carbon film.
An aluminum film deposited on a self-supporting carbon
film (10 ug/cm2) and overcoated with 5 nm of silver
was used for determination of the aluminum cross
sections.
The thickness of the aluminum film was 5 keV for 3-MeV
He-4 ions.
To measure F-19 cross section a Na-F film (10 ug/cm2)
evaporated on a self-supporting carbon film
(10 ug/cm2) overcoated with 10 nm of silver was used.
A natural abundance magnesium thin film (45 nm)
deposited on a self-supporting carbon film (10 ug/cm2)
and overcoated with 5 nm of gold was used for
magnesium cross section measurements.
The silicon target is a natural abundant Si-O thin film
(10 ug/cm2) deposited on a self-supporting carbon film
(10 ug/cm2) and also overcoated with 6 nm of silver,
the chlorine target is a natural abundant 50 nm
Ba-Cl/2 film evaporated on a self-supporting carbon
film.
Two surface barrier detector
The uncertainty in the cross section is
reported by authors.
All data were taken from Sigma Data Base (ISU)
Checked and approved by Cheng Huan-Sheng
Last checking has been done.
